						BBBBB	  PPPPPPP    MMM MMM
						B    B	  P     P    M  M  M
						BBBBBB	  P     P    M     M
						B    BB	  PPPPPPP    M     M
						B     B	  P	     M     M
						BBBBBBB	  P	     M     M



Description
===========
Bash Password Manager is a script that create a database
in which you can store your passwords in a total secure way!
The database is double encrypted with GPG and OpenSSL so you can be sure that
nobody can hack/view/compromise your database :)


Requirements
============
bash   : it is a bash script ;)
zenity : message dialogs
gpg    : encrypt/decrypt db
openssl: encrypt/decrypt db


How it works
============
The script will create and encrypt the DB. 
After that you can add, view or store new password.
This script has lot of features such:
	* double encryption
	* possibility to choose your favourite cipher-algo (aes256, blowfish, twofish, ecc)
	* possibility to generate strong random password
	* possibility to change the cipher-algo of your DB when you want
	* this script is small and fast


How to use
==========
Go to Applications -> Accessories -> BashPWDman


How to install
==============
Download the archive and after you have extract it,
open the terminal and type:
chmod +x PATH_TO_EXTRACTED_FOLDER/install
sudo PATH_TO_EXTRACTED_FOLDER/install


Extra options
=============================
Open the terminal and type:
bashpwdm -v -> view version of Bash PWD Manager
bashpwdm -c -> change the cipher-algo of db
bashpwdm -p -> create a strong password


Notes
=====
For more information see:
<http://projects.polslinux.it>
